reviewText: It is very informative and interesting  about the past of Carmel and a life's of the pioneers in it.
it is the coolest VHS tape around - everyone should see it - Clint is great, as always - anyone interested in Hemmingway et al needs to see this.

I bought this movie several years ago when i was in Carmel.
 I enjoyed all the stories so much that i started doing
my own research. I've since collected several books of poetry by
George Sterling (most autographed). It was an interesting movie,
and obviously an inspiration to me.
